18:26.858 --> 18:29.527
It makes sense.
That's when Mom and Dad died.

18:29.569 --> 18:32.071
He wants to start
a family of his own.

18:32.071 --> 18:33.615
Check out the cake.

18:33.656 --> 18:36.409
There's only
a little groom on top.

18:56.387 --> 18:57.597
You're late.

18:57.639 --> 18:59.933
I'm sorry.

18:59.933 --> 19:01.559
I just couldn't do it.

19:03.895 --> 19:06.773
If you need some more time,
I guess I can wait.

19:08.441 --> 19:11.319
No, I don't need
more time, Robbie.

19:11.361 --> 19:12.737
I don't ever want to marry you.

19:17.283 --> 19:18.660
You know, that information...

19:18.701 --> 19:22.038
might have been a little
more useful to me yesterday.

19:23.957 --> 19:25.959
I've been talking to my friends
the last couple of days...

19:26.000 --> 19:27.794
Here it comes.

19:27.836 --> 19:31.422
And I think I figured out
what's been bothering me.

19:31.464 --> 19:33.591
I'm not in love with Robbie now.

19:33.633 --> 19:37.220
I'm in love with Robbie
six years ago...

19:37.262 --> 19:39.430
Robbie, the lead singer
of Final Warning...

19:39.472 --> 19:41.432
when I used to come and
watch you from the front row...

19:41.474 --> 19:43.601
in your spandex pants...

19:43.643 --> 19:45.770
your silk shirt unbuttoned...

19:47.146 --> 19:49.858
licking the microphone
like David Lee Roth.

19:49.899 --> 19:52.318
I still got the spandex.
I'll put them on right now.

19:52.360 --> 19:54.237
The point is,
I woke up this morning...

19:54.279 --> 19:57.615
and I realized I'm about
to marry a wedding singer.

19:57.657 --> 20:00.118
I am never going
to leave Ridgefield.

20:00.160 --> 20:02.078
Why do you need
to leave Ridgefield?

20:02.120 --> 20:05.165
We grew up here.
All our friends are here.

20:05.206 --> 20:07.333
It's the perfect place
to raise a family.

20:07.375 --> 20:09.878
Living in your sister's
basement with five kids...

20:09.919 --> 20:11.713
while you're off every
weekend doing wedding gigs...

20:11.754 --> 20:13.673
at a whopping 60 bucks a pop?

20:13.715 --> 20:15.216
Once again...

20:15.258 --> 20:17.177
things that could have been
brought to my attention...

20:17.177 --> 20:18.303
yesterday!

20:21.181 --> 20:23.433
The fact is,
we grew apart a long time ago.

20:24.601 --> 20:27.020
You wanted to get married.
You didn't care to who.

20:27.061 --> 20:30.273
That's not true. I love you.
Come here.

20:30.315 --> 20:33.818
I want to spend
the rest of my life with you.

20:33.860 --> 20:36.279
Hey, Linda.

20:36.321 --> 20:38.323
You're a bitch.

20:41.493 --> 20:44.037
Thanks, Petey.
Go back to the house.

20:46.956 --> 20:49.250
He might have
Tourette's syndrome.

20:49.292 --> 20:50.668
We're looking into it.

20:53.171 --> 20:54.464
I got to go.

20:57.550 --> 20:58.676
I'm sorry.

21:13.942 --> 21:16.486
Ninety-nine Luftballons...

21:19.531 --> 21:20.698
Glenn!

21:20.740 --> 21:22.951
Don't be so jumpy.

21:22.992 --> 21:25.203
These are for you.

21:25.245 --> 21:26.704
Thank you.

21:28.623 --> 21:30.708
They're beautiful.

21:32.168 --> 21:34.337
I have something else for you.

21:38.675 --> 21:41.636
Two airplane tickets
to Las Vegas?

21:45.515 --> 21:47.559
Oh, my God, Glenn!

21:49.227 --> 21:50.395
I know you wanted
to set a date...

21:50.436 --> 21:52.564
so I went to the travel agent
and set it.

21:53.940 --> 21:56.192
Glenn, I love you so much...

21:56.234 --> 21:57.360
but Las Vegas? I thought--

21:57.402 --> 21:59.445
Jules, it's the romance
capital of the world.

21:59.487 --> 22:02.073
I just don't want
a big wedding--

22:02.115 --> 22:03.783
hundreds of people
we don't know...

22:03.825 --> 22:05.827
that are just there
for the free drinks...

22:05.869 --> 22:07.912
and all-you-can-eat buffet.

22:07.954 --> 22:09.956
They might as well be in Vegas.

22:16.421 --> 22:19.549
Las Vegas it is,
and it'll be great.

22:21.301 --> 22:23.136
Are you going to do
the girl thing?

22:23.178 --> 22:26.472
You're going to act happy
and be pouting on the inside?

22:27.974 --> 22:29.642
I'm happy.

22:34.480 --> 22:35.815
All right.

22:35.815 --> 22:37.483
Let's get married here.

22:37.525 --> 22:40.403
I know that's what you want.

22:40.445 --> 22:42.322
Thank you, Glenn.

22:43.656 --> 22:45.158
It's more important
to you anyway.

22:46.659 --> 22:49.287
I promise I will give you
the most beautiful wedding...

22:49.329 --> 22:51.331
and even you'll have
a good time.

23:15.647 --> 23:18.149
It's about time
his best friend showed up.

23:18.191 --> 23:19.943
So, how's he doing?

23:19.984 --> 23:21.402
I don't know.

23:21.444 --> 23:24.489
He's been down in the basement
since it happened.

23:24.531 --> 23:26.533
Five days now.

23:26.533 --> 23:30.745
I think he's having some kind
of a mental situation...

23:30.787 --> 23:33.289
an episode or something.

23:33.331 --> 23:34.749
All right.

23:37.210 --> 23:39.170
You do something, because
I don't want to be known...

23:39.212 --> 23:41.464
as the brother-in-law
of the town nut job.

23:41.506 --> 23:42.924
I got enough problems already.

23:42.966 --> 23:45.134
Shit,
I got water all over myself.

23:53.935 --> 23:55.436
Hello?

24:00.817 --> 24:02.485
You all right?

24:10.160 --> 24:13.037
These sheets are soft.
You use Downy?

24:15.081 --> 24:17.417
All Tempa-Cheer.

24:17.417 --> 24:19.419
You can wash your clothes
at any temperature...

24:19.419 --> 24:21.421
and the colors
don't run together.

24:21.421 --> 24:24.674
-Really?
-Yeah. Now leave me alone.

24:26.259 --> 24:28.344
You have to go back to work.

24:28.386 --> 24:31.598
There's going to be over
a hundred drunk girls...

24:31.639 --> 24:32.765
at this wedding tonight.

24:32.807 --> 24:34.350
I've got nothing
to offer anybody.

24:34.392 --> 24:37.687
I haven't done jack shit
since high school.

24:37.729 --> 24:39.731
Why would any girl
ever marry me?

24:39.772 --> 24:41.482
Marry you?

24:41.524 --> 24:43.526
I'm just trying to get someone
to play with your ding-dong.

24:47.864 --> 24:49.949
Holiday...

24:52.118 --> 24:54.370
Celebrate...

25:05.340 --> 25:08.301
If we took a holiday...

25:09.677 --> 25:12.013
Took some time to celebrate...

25:12.055 --> 25:13.973
Come on, let's celebrate.

25:14.015 --> 25:16.559
Just one day out of life...

25:18.228 --> 25:20.438
It would be...

25:20.480 --> 25:23.816
It would be so nice.

25:23.816 --> 25:27.403
Everybody spread the word.

25:27.445 --> 25:31.741
I live in
my sister's basement.

25:32.909 --> 25:35.078
He just had his heart broken.

25:35.119 --> 25:37.914
Why would he even think
about coming back to work?

25:37.956 --> 25:39.582
I don't know.

25:39.624 --> 25:42.252
Celebrate.

25:53.429 --> 25:55.974
You guys are off
to a great start.

25:56.015 --> 25:57.517
I mean...

25:57.559 --> 26:00.228
Cindy showed up,
so, right away, Scott...

26:00.270 --> 26:01.688
you got to be pretty psyched.

26:03.106 --> 26:05.650
I'm not paying you to hear
your thoughts on life.

26:05.692 --> 26:07.026
I'm paying you to sing.

26:08.695 --> 26:12.198
I have a microphone,
and you don't...

26:12.240 --> 26:15.160
so you will listen
to every damn word...

26:15.201 --> 26:16.953
I have to say!

26:23.877 --> 26:28.339
It's funny. Some of us
will never find true love.

26:28.381 --> 26:32.135
Like, take, for instance...me.

26:33.344 --> 26:35.305
And I'm pretty sure
that guy right there.

26:37.473 --> 26:39.726
And that lady
with the sideburns.

26:41.603 --> 26:44.189
And basically
everybody at table nine.

26:45.607 --> 26:47.901
But the worst thing is...

26:47.901 --> 26:53.907
that me, fatty,
sideburns lady...

26:53.948 --> 26:55.742
and the mutants
over at table nine...

26:57.785 --> 27:01.080
will never, ever find a way
to better the situation...

27:01.080 --> 27:03.208
because...

27:03.249 --> 27:06.920
apparently, we have
absolutely nothing to offer...

27:06.961 --> 27:08.505
the opposite sex.

27:10.131 --> 27:12.592
You are the worst wedding singer
in the world, buddy!

27:12.634 --> 27:14.719
Sir, one more outburst...

27:14.761 --> 27:17.138
I will strangle you
with my microphone wire.

27:20.016 --> 27:21.809
Let's cut the stupid cake...

27:21.851 --> 27:23.770
because the fat guy's
going to have a heart attack...

27:23.811 --> 27:25.188
if we don't eat again soon.

27:27.524 --> 27:31.319
And while we do that,
here's a little mood music.

27:38.785 --> 27:41.412
Cindy and Scott are newlyweds.

27:47.168 --> 27:49.587
He loves her...

27:49.629 --> 27:52.257
But she loves
this guy right here...

27:52.298 --> 27:54.926
And he loves somebody else.

27:54.968 --> 27:57.887
You just can't win.

27:57.929 --> 27:59.889
And so it goes...

27:59.931 --> 28:02.851
Until the day you die.

28:02.892 --> 28:05.353
This thing they call love...

28:05.395 --> 28:07.647
Is gonna make you cry.

28:07.689 --> 28:08.857
I hate you.

28:08.898 --> 28:10.942
I've had the blues...

28:10.984 --> 28:13.778
The reds and the pinks.

28:13.820 --> 28:16.447
One thing's for sure...

28:17.490 --> 28:18.491
Love stinks?

28:18.491 --> 28:20.118
Love stinks.

28:42.056 --> 28:44.475
Drug addict! Degenerate!

29:12.837 --> 29:15.840
I was wondering
what happened to you.

29:17.759 --> 29:19.677
Did everybody leave?

29:20.887 --> 29:23.223
Pretty much,
except for a few cops...

29:23.264 --> 29:25.850
that are still interviewing
some witnesses.

29:30.647 --> 29:32.815
I'm going to get
the hell out of here.

29:34.984 --> 29:36.569
So it was
your first wedding back.

29:36.611 --> 29:38.947
Of course things are going
to be a little shaky.

29:38.988 --> 29:41.533
A little shaky?
I hate weddings.

29:41.574 --> 29:44.786
I hate the bride.
I hate the groom.

29:44.828 --> 29:47.872
I want them to be miserable,
because that's what I am.

29:47.914 --> 29:49.916
No. You're the best.

29:49.916 --> 29:53.503
At what? People eat
prime rib, and I sing.

29:53.545 --> 29:57.048
It's a joke.
I can't do this anymore.

29:58.049 --> 30:00.927
Glenn and I set the date...

30:00.969 --> 30:02.929
so you have to play our wedding.

30:05.056 --> 30:06.558
Congratulations.

30:07.809 --> 30:11.896
I just can't do it, all right?

30:12.939 --> 30:15.400
I'm having an engagement party
in two weeks...

30:15.441 --> 30:17.652
and I really want
you and Sammy to come.

30:39.174 --> 30:41.176
Good, you're here.

30:41.217 --> 30:43.678
Robbie's here!
Let's move it!

30:43.720 --> 30:45.597
The kids have been fed,
but if they want snacks...

30:45.638 --> 30:48.975
there's ice pops in the freezer,
or microwave popcorn.

30:48.975 --> 30:50.310
Good.

30:50.351 --> 30:51.936
Are you going
to the engagement party?

30:51.978 --> 30:53.771
Yeah, I'll probably go.

30:55.148 --> 30:57.483
Come on, Andy, move your ass!

30:57.483 --> 30:59.444
Hang on. I'm watching Dallas.

30:59.485 --> 31:01.946
I think J.R. might be dead.
They shot him.

31:01.988 --> 31:02.947
Good night.

31:02.989 --> 31:04.991
-Love you.
-Love you.

31:05.033 --> 31:07.118
Time to make the donuts.

31:07.160 --> 31:08.286
I made the donuts.

31:08.328 --> 31:11.164
Dunkin' donuts--
up to 52 varieties...

31:11.206 --> 31:12.999
Uncle Robbie's here.

31:14.834 --> 31:17.629
Hey, the Goofball Brothers.

31:17.670 --> 31:20.298
ls it true you're in the middle
of a nervous breakdown?

31:23.301 --> 31:26.471
-Who said that?
-Everybody.

31:26.513 --> 31:28.848
You're eight years old.
You only know your parents.

31:28.848 --> 31:30.141
What are you talking about?

31:30.183 --> 31:32.936
Is it true you're gonna end up
in a mental institution?

31:32.977 --> 31:35.104
Cuckoo's nest!

31:36.272 --> 31:37.565
Hey, kids.

31:39.776 --> 31:41.611
Remember what we talked about?

31:43.947 --> 31:45.782
Go over there
and watch some television.

31:45.824 --> 31:47.700
Can I speak to you for a second?

31:47.700 --> 31:49.327
Everybody...

31:52.205 --> 31:54.207
I've been thinking
about what happened to you...

31:54.249 --> 31:55.708
and it's all for the best.

31:55.750 --> 31:58.336
I know you were
in love and everything...

31:58.378 --> 31:59.462
but that wears off.

31:59.504 --> 32:02.924
Me and your sister,
we used to be wild.

32:02.966 --> 32:05.009
She was very adventurous...

32:05.051 --> 32:07.971
and we got into some crazy shit.

32:08.012 --> 32:09.681
But now the thrill is gone.

32:09.722 --> 32:13.017
If we get a second alone,
we usually go to sleep.

32:13.059 --> 32:15.645
If it's a special occasion...

32:15.687 --> 32:18.523
she might do
this exotic dance for me.

32:18.565 --> 32:20.024
What?

32:20.066 --> 32:23.486
Sometimes she might
work with my nipples a bit.

32:23.528 --> 32:25.280
All right, enough. Go out.

32:25.321 --> 32:27.157
I'll take care of the kids.

32:28.408 --> 32:31.411
I don't know what I just said,
but I said something.

32:39.878 --> 32:41.504
Women got a thing
about marriage.

32:41.546 --> 32:45.800
If you want to stay with them,
you're gonna have to marry them.

32:45.842 --> 32:48.094
No big deal. There she is.

32:48.136 --> 32:50.513
The girl who finally beat me
into submission.

32:50.555 --> 32:51.681
That's right.

32:51.723 --> 32:54.017
August 5th
is less than three months away.

32:54.058 --> 32:56.186
We've got a lot of planning
to do.

32:56.227 --> 32:58.229
Do you think
it would be better...

32:58.271 --> 33:01.107
if maybe you took over
all the arrangements?

33:01.107 --> 33:04.569
I'd like to do it together.

33:04.611 --> 33:07.822
Yeah, but you like this stuff.

33:07.864 --> 33:09.365
It's really not my thing.

33:10.909 --> 33:13.453
God forbid I screw up
the wedding flowers.

33:13.495 --> 33:14.871
How could I live with myself?

33:14.913 --> 33:16.080
He'll be so wasted...

33:16.122 --> 33:19.292
he won't know flowers
are at the wedding.

33:21.961 --> 33:24.214
I hear you're gonna have
your bachelor party Friday.

33:24.255 --> 33:28.426
Gonna be all right with that?
You might miss Miami Vice.

33:28.468 --> 33:31.930
Nope. Summer. Reruns.
I'm all set.

33:31.971 --> 33:34.390
Great.

33:37.310 --> 33:39.562
All right, nice house.

33:39.604 --> 33:42.607
I told you this guy was loaded.

33:42.649 --> 33:45.985
I know. In and out, though.
I don't want to be here long.

33:45.985 --> 33:48.655
Let me just pick up a chick,
and we'll get out of here.

33:48.696 --> 33:50.448
What do you think
of the jacket?

33:50.490 --> 33:54.118
I would lose that glove.
You look nuts.

33:54.160 --> 33:56.287
There's Julia.

33:57.956 --> 34:00.041
Let's go say hello.

34:01.334 --> 34:03.461
Hi, you guys.

34:03.503 --> 34:05.213
I'm so glad you came.

34:05.255 --> 34:07.507
Jason,
this is Robbie and Sammy...

34:07.549 --> 34:10.009
and this is my fiance Glenn.

34:10.051 --> 34:12.303
-Congratulations, Glenn.
-Thank you.

34:12.344 --> 34:13.471
Robbie Hart.

34:13.513 --> 34:17.266
I heard what happened
to you at your wedding.

34:17.308 --> 34:20.311
That was so cold.
You must have felt like shit.

34:20.353 --> 34:24.607
No. It felt really good.
Thanks for bringing it up.

34:24.649 --> 34:27.527
My parents died when I was 10.
Want to talk about that?

34:27.527 --> 34:29.696
Why would we want
to talk about that?

34:29.737 --> 34:31.197
I don't know.

34:31.197 --> 34:32.824
Somebody needs a drink.

34:32.866 --> 34:35.034
Actually,
I'm not a big drinker.

34:35.076 --> 34:36.870
I am.
How about an Alabama Slammer?

34:36.911 --> 34:38.036
Sounds like a plan.

34:38.079 --> 34:40.039
Meet me at the bar.
I gotta piss first.

34:40.039 --> 34:42.333
Have a few drinks
and drive home.

34:44.543 --> 34:46.838
Julia, thanks for inviting us.

34:46.880 --> 34:49.716
I'm glad you guys came.
We hang out at work so much...

34:49.716 --> 34:51.967
but we don't get to talk
'cause we're always so busy.

34:53.678 --> 34:55.847
We should make time to talk,
don't you think?

34:58.349 --> 35:01.603
Know what? The first time
this guy saw you...

35:01.644 --> 35:03.897
he told me
he was gonna hit on you.

35:03.938 --> 35:06.524
-Really?
-That's not true.

35:06.566 --> 35:09.360
Yeah, it is.
You told me she was in trouble.

35:09.402 --> 35:12.197
She was gonna get it,
and she didn't even know it.

35:12.238 --> 35:14.199
He's teasing.
I would never say that.

35:14.240 --> 35:16.868
You said you were
gonna give it to her.

35:16.910 --> 35:18.870
Give me what, exactly?

35:18.912 --> 35:20.455
You're a jerk.

35:20.497 --> 35:22.916
What do you mean?
You didn't know she was engaged.

35:22.916 --> 35:24.834
So now you're not
gonna give it to me?

35:24.876 --> 35:26.544
Very funny.

35:26.586 --> 35:28.046
Say hi to your brother Tito.

35:32.926 --> 35:34.886
So how are you doing?

35:34.928 --> 35:37.972
I'm doing better. I don't know.

35:38.014 --> 35:40.433
How are you and Glenn doing
with the wedding plans?

35:43.228 --> 35:46.606
Glenn isn't really--
He's very busy right now.

35:46.648 --> 35:50.735
He works on Wall Street.
You know how that is nowadays.

35:50.777 --> 35:53.780
Wall Street--stocks and stuff?

35:53.780 --> 35:54.906
Actually, he's in bonds.

35:54.948 --> 35:58.368
He barely has time to sleep,
let alone plan a wedding...

35:58.409 --> 36:00.078
so I'm kind of doing this
on my own.

36:00.119 --> 36:03.164
But I went to Marshall's
for the floral centerpieces.

36:03.206 --> 36:05.667
Marshall's?
You should go to Tony's.

36:05.708 --> 36:08.378
They're cheaper, and
they've got a great selection.

36:08.419 --> 36:11.422
All right.
Well, thank you for the tip.

36:11.464 --> 36:13.758
It's a shame you won't be
doing weddings anymore.

36:13.800 --> 36:15.134
We won't get
to hang out as much.

36:15.176 --> 36:17.554
We'll get to hang out.

36:17.595 --> 36:20.974
There's other things to do
besides weddings, right?

36:22.809 --> 36:25.270
Oy, oy, bar mitzvah...

36:25.311 --> 36:27.438
Mazel tov...

36:47.167 --> 36:48.293
L'chaim !

36:48.334 --> 36:51.504
Let's keep the fun rolling.
Take it away, George.

37:04.601 --> 37:07.812
Do you really want to hurt me?

37:11.024 --> 37:12.442
You seem kind of sad.

37:12.483 --> 37:14.152
Why don't you
get out there and dance?

37:14.194 --> 37:17.572
I asked that girl over there.
She turned me down.

37:17.614 --> 37:20.533
She said she didn't dance
with losers.

37:20.575 --> 37:23.286
Man. That hurts.

37:23.328 --> 37:26.206
But why would you want
to dance with somebody...

37:26.206 --> 37:28.875
who doesn't want
to dance with you? Right?

37:30.168 --> 37:32.003
Listen, don't worry.

37:32.045 --> 37:34.631
You're gonna meet a girl
who treats you right someday.

37:34.672 --> 37:36.007
I promise you.

37:37.550 --> 37:39.677
How you guys doing?
All right?

37:39.719 --> 37:41.846
I want you to meet
a friend of mine...

37:41.888 --> 37:43.681
by the name of Julia Sullivan.

37:45.016 --> 37:47.477
Could you come out here
for a second?

37:48.853 --> 37:50.021
Say hi to Julia, everybody.

37:50.063 --> 37:51.105
Hello.

37:51.147 --> 37:54.359
Now, who of you out there
would like to dance...

37:54.400 --> 37:55.902
with this fine-looking woman?

37:59.113 --> 38:02.158
I'd like to do more
than dance with her.

